                  <h2><font color="#990000"> <!--0.04 -->
	                  <a href="http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/wingnut/2010/05/what-no-parachutes.asp">What, No Parachutes?</a></font></h2>
                  

               <div style="clear:both;"></div><p>I have accomplished the following steps for all blog but this one:</p> <ol> <li>Established a common blog template format.&nbsp; This post is in a variation of that format.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; </li> <li>Republished those blogs for which the format is to be changed on all prior posts and archives.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; </li> <li>Posted “hiatus” messages indicating that the blog is now separated from the Blogger service and will be silent until a new blog engine is put in place.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; </li> <li>Backed up the hosted forms of the blogs on the web sites where they had been published, up until now, using Blogger FTP publishing.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; </li> <li>Exported the Blogger content for the blogs.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </li> <li>Deleted the blog from Blogger.</li></ol> <p>With completion of this post, I will carry out steps (5-6) for <em>Spanner Wingnut</em> as well.</p> <p>The next post you see will be from attempts to use a new blog engine installed on my web site itself.</p>  <div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div><p class="blogger-labels">Labels: <a rel='tag' href="http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/wingnut/labels/blog%20development.asp">blog development</a></p>
 
	           <p class="byline"><a href="http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/wingnut/2010/05/what-no-parachutes.asp" title="permalink">&para;</a>
	              posted by orcmid 
                  at <a href="http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/wingnut/2010/05/what-no-parachutes.asp" title="permalink">5/01/2010 01:39:00 AM</a>
                  </p>
       
               
               
